<p><b>Dream interpretation</b> is the process of assigning meaning to <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dream" title=3D"Dream">dreams</a>. In m=
any ancient societies, such as those of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Ancient_Egypt" title=3D"Ancient Egypt">Egypt</a> and <a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ancient_Greece" title=3D"Ancient Greece">Greece</a=
>, dreaming was considered a supernatural communication or a means of <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miracle" title=3D"Miracle">divine inter=
vention</a>, whose message could be interpreted by people with these associ=
ated spiritual powers.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dream_interpretation#cite_note-1"><span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=
 In the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modern_era" title=3D"Moder=
n era">modern era</a>, various schools of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Psychology" title=3D"Psychology">psychology</a> and <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neurobiology" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Neur=
obiology">neurobiology</a> have offered theories about the meaning and purp=
ose of dreams.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dream_interpretation#cite_note-2"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Dream_interpretation#cite_note-3"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>3<=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
